Question:4 Explore and write short notes on any three Data Science frameworks 
Ans: A Data Science framework is a set of tools, libraries, and best practices 
that provides a structured environment for building, training, and deploying 
data-driven models. Frameworks simplify complex tasks like data 
preprocessing, machine learning, deep learning, and model deployment, 
allowing data scientists to focus on solving problems rather than reinventing 
code. 
Key Features of Frameworks: 
• Reusable components for ML and data analysis. 
• Support for large-scale data processing. 
• Integration with visualization and deployment tools. 
• Optimization for speed and efficiency (CPU/GPU support). 
Three Popular Data Science Frameworks 
1. TensorFlow 
• Type: Open-source machine learning and deep learning framework. 
• Developer: Google Brain. 
• Purpose: Build and deploy neural networks and ML models. 
• Key Features: 
o Dataflow graphs for efficient computation. 
o Supports CPU, GPU, and TPU acceleration. 
