o Scalable for large datasets and production. 
• Use Cases: Image recognition, NLP, recommendation systems. 
• Pros: Highly scalable, production-ready, large community. 
• Cons: Steeper learning curve for beginners. 
2. PyTorch 
• Type: Open-source deep learning framework. 
• Developer: Facebook AI Research (FAIR). 
• Purpose: Research, prototyping, and building deep learning models. 
• Key Features: 
o Dynamic computation graphs (eager execution) for flexibility. 
o GPU acceleration with CUDA. 
o Pre-trained model libraries (TorchVision, HuggingFace). 
o TorchServe for deployment. 
• Use Cases: Computer vision, NLP, reinforcement learning. 
• Pros: Intuitive, easy to debug, widely used in research. 
• Cons: Deployment tools are less mature compared to TensorFlow. 
3. Scikit-learn 
• Type: Open-source machine learning library for Python. 
• Developer: Community-driven (Python ecosystem). 
• Purpose: Classical machine learning tasks. 
• Key Features: 
o Implements regression, classification, clustering, and 
