Question 5: Identify different roles in Data Science (e.g., Data Analyst, Data Scientist, 
ML Engineer) and their responsibilities. 
Ans: 5 
1. Data Analyst 
Focus: Interpreting data to generate actionable insights. 
Responsibilities: 
• Collect, clean, and organize data from various sources. 
• Analyze data using statistical methods and tools (Excel, SQL, Python, 
R). 
• Create visualizations (charts, dashboards) to communicate trends and 
patterns. 
• Generate reports to support business decisions. 
• Often works closely with business stakeholders to answer specific 
questions. 
Key Skills: SQL, Excel, Tableau/Power BI, basic statistics, data cleaning, 
visualization. 
2. Data Scientist 
Focus: Extracting insights and building predictive models using data. 
Responsibilities: 
• Explore and analyze large datasets to find patterns and trends. 
• Build machine learning models for prediction, classification, or 
clustering. 
