• Work on data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model 
evaluation. 
• Communicate results to stakeholders and suggest data-driven 
decisions. 
• May also create experiments and hypotheses to test business 
strategies. 
Key Skills: Python/R, SQL, machine learning, statistics, data visualization, 
big data tools (Spark, Hadoop), deep learning (optional). 
3. Machine Learning (ML) Engineer 
Focus: Deploying and scaling machine learning models in production. 
Responsibilities: 
• Take ML models from prototypes (developed by data scientists) to 
production-ready systems. 
• Optimize models for performance, scalability, and reliability. 
• Work on model monitoring, retraining, and maintenance. 
• Collaborate with software engineers and data engineers to integrate 
ML pipelines. 
Key Skills: Python, TensorFlow/PyTorch, cloud platforms 
(AWS/GCP/Azure), APIs, software engineering, DevOps. 
4. Data Engineer 
Focus: Building and maintaining the data infrastructure. 
Responsibilities: 
• Design, construct, and maintain data pipelines and databases. 
• Ensure data quality, reliability, and accessibility. 
• Work with big data frameworks like Spark, Hadoop, or Kafka. 
• Support data scientists and analysts by providing clean, structured 
data. 
Key Skills: SQL, Python/Java/Scala, ETL tools, data warehousing, big data 
technologies, cloud platforms. 
